    "analysis": "Metric analysis (previous step) found widespread, strong socket-related anomalies: many components (rabbitmq, rabbitmq-exporter, carts-db, orders-db, catalogue-db, queue-master, session-db and the catalogue and payment services) have values in the incident window at or above their global P95. Disk I/O flags are non-actionable zeros. Memory shows only small, isolated increases. Traces and error_logs are empty, so trace-based localization and error log inspection are not available. Given the broad, simultaneous socket anomalies across messaging and DB components, the hypothesis is a network/socket-layer failure. To confirm and localize the root-cause service/component and reason, we need to analyze log.csv (log.error_count and other log KPIs) for the candidate components to see which service(s) show error spikes or related indicators during the incident window.",
