{
    "analysis": "Previous steps: we loaded all telemetry and computed global percentiles per component-KPI. Metric analysis shows strong, simultaneous socket anomalies across messaging and DB components (rabbitmq, rabbitmq-exporter, carts-db, orders-db, catalogue-db, queue-master, session-db). Among service-level components from the allowed set, catalogue and payment show elevated socket counts in the incident window (catalogue: 20/25 hits, earliest 2024-01-20 22:36:00+00:00; payment: 12/25 hits, earliest 2024-01-20 22:44:00+00:00). Log analysis shows meaningful row-count spikes (log.row_count) at ~22:36 for front-end, user, queue-master, catalogue, orders, payment, shipping; log.error_count is zero-baseline. Traces and error_logs are empty, so we must rely on metrics+logs. The evidence so far suggests a socket/network-level problem affecting many infra components (DBs, RabbitMQ) and service-level socket counts, with catalogue showing an early and strong service-level socket anomaly coincident with log.row_count spikes at ~22:36. We need a compact confirmation focused on the allowed service candidates (carts, catalogue, orders, payment, user) showing their socket and relevant metric/log anomaly counts and earliest timestamps inside the incident window to localize the root cause service.",
